#Role: Global Admininstrator 

## ğŸ” Purpose

The Global Administrator has the highest level of access in Microsoft Entra. This role can manage all aspects of the directory and is typically reserved for a small number of trusted individuals.

## ğŸ› ï¸ Key Responsibilities 

- Create, edit, delete users, groups, and roles
- Assign admin roles to other users
- Configure identity governance, security settings, and compliance policies
- Access and manage all Microsoft 365 services tied to the tenant
- Reset passwords for all users and admins

## ğŸ” Permissions & Scope
- Full access to all Entra features and services
- Can elevate access for Priviledged Identity Management (PIM)
- Can delegate other admin roles, which includes making custom roles
- Should be protected with MFA and monitored via Conditional access 

## âš ï¸ Best practices

- Limit to 2-4 users per tenant
- Use PIM for just in time access
- Montior Sign ins and audit logs regularly
- Avoid using Global admin for daily tasks - assign least privilege roles instead.

## ğŸ—ƒï¸ Related Tools

- Microsoft Entra Admin Center
- Microsoft 365 Admin Center
- Powershell (MSgraph & AzureAD modules)
- Mictosoft Defender for Identity

## ğŸŒŸ Important notes

- Global admin overrides all other roles
- Required for initial setup for Entra ID and tenant-wide configurations
- Often used in break glass scenarios


